                </h2>
                <p className="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                  <strong>Ripple</strong> is a San Francisco-based private fintech company that
                  develops payment solutions built on the XRP Ledger. While Ripple does not
                  control the decentralized XRPL network, it is the most prominent commercial
                  entity building on and advocating for XRP. Ripple&apos;s flagship product,{' '}
                  <strong>RippleNet</strong>, connects banks and payment providers to enable
                  real-time gross settlement across borders using XRP as an optional bridge
                  currency (On-Demand Liquidity, or ODL).
                </p>
                <p className="mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                  Ripple has signed partnerships with over <strong>300 financial institutions
                  and payment providers</strong> across more than 55 countries, including
                  Santander, SBI Holdings (Japan), Standard Chartered, and PNC Bank. ODL
                  customers use XRP to eliminate the need for pre-funded nostro accounts in
                  destination currencies — a long-standing cost center in correspondent banking
                  that can tie up billions in working capital globally.
                </p>
                <p className="leading-relaxed">
                  Ripple is a private company and has resisted calls to go public, particularly
                  during the period of regulatory uncertainty created by the SEC lawsuit.
                  Following the resolution of that case, Ripple has resumed expansion into
                  institutional DeFi, tokenization, and stablecoin infrastructure.
                </p>
