                  In <strong>December 2024</strong>, Ripple launched <strong>RLUSD</strong> — a
                  USD-collateralized stablecoin issued on both the XRP Ledger and Ethereum.
                  RLUSD is regulated under the New York Department of Financial Services (NYDFS)
                  framework, making it one of the first stablecoins issued by a major crypto
